# Teaching CS Fundamentals Maker with micro:bit


#### Bring hands-on technology learning to Computer Science with our Maker course, designed around the micro:bit physical computing device. The micro:bit course bridges the gap between digital and physical worlds, and enables students to transfer their computer programs into real-world applications. 

<img src="https://images.code.org/5866a20822d995085942c3b454a49cf0-image-1709135732635.png" alt="Image CS Discoveries students" width="225px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 40px 00px 40px;">


## In this module, you will:

* #### Prepare to teach foundational coding concepts like events, loops, conditionals, variables and functions.
* #### Gain practical experience in how hardware and software can work together. 
* #### Practice key concepts included in the unit.
* #### Prepare to teach any of the CS Fundamentals Maker with micro:bit courses. 

<br>


#### **Note:** The CS Maker modules are divided into four courses: **grades 2-5**. This professional learning module will prepare you to teach any of the **beginner pathways** and provide the option of experiencing one or many grade-levels depending on your needs.

